fr.sii.ogham.core.sender

Class MultiImplementationSender<M extends Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.core.sender.MultiImplementationSender<M>
  • Type Parameters:
    M - The type of message that the implementations can handle
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConditionalSender, MessageSender
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EmailSender, SmsSender

    public class MultiImplementationSender<M extends Message>
extends Object
implements ConditionalSender
    Decorator sender that is able to handle a particular type of message. And for handling this message it can rely on several possible implementations. Each implementation is associated to a Condition. The condition indicates at runtime if the message can be handled by the possible implementation. There can be any kind of condition (for example, based on a required class in the classpath or a particular property value...). The implementation selection is done in the supports(Message) method.
